  <div class="hero-row">
    <div class="hero-text">
      <h1>{{ site.name }}</h1>
      <p class="role">{{ site.role }}<br>{{ site.affiliation }}</p>
    </div>
    <img class="headshot" src="/images/headshot.jpg" width="432" height="528" alt="Headshot of John Langford">
  </div>
  <p class="lede">I work on issues at the heart of a free press and a functioning democracy — <strong>the First Amendment, news-gathering, free expression, and disinformation</strong>. This site is where I write about them.</p>
</section>

<section id="writing">
  <div class="section-label">
    <span class="glyph">§</span>
    <span class="mono">Writing</span>
  </div>

  <ul class="post-list">
    {%- for post in collections.post | reverse %}
    <li>
      <a class="post-link" href="{{ post.url }}">
        <time datetime="{{ post.date | isoDateShort }}">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</time>
        <span class="post-title">{{ post.data.title }}</span>
        {%- if post.data.description %}
        <span class="post-sub">{{ post.data.description }}</span>
        {%- endif %}
      </a>
    </li>
    {%- endfor %}
  </ul>
</section>

<section id="about" class="about">
  <div class="section-label">
    <span class="glyph">§</span>
    <span class="mono">About</span>
  </div>
  <p>John Langford is a Visiting Clinical Associate Professor of Law at Yale Law School.</p>
  <p>Before joining the law school, he was counsel at Protect Democracy, where he focused primarily on issues related to the First Amendment, news-gathering, free expression, and disinformation. Prior to joining Protect Democracy, Langford was a Clinical Lecturer in Law, Associate Research Scholar in Law, and the Floyd Abrams Fellow and Staff Attorney for the Media Freedom and Information Access Clinic at Yale Law School. He previously clerked for the Honorable Robin S. Rosenbaum on the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit and worked as a litigation associate at Wilmer Cutler Pickering Hale and Dorr LLP.</p>
  <p>At Yale, he teaches in the Media Freedom &amp; Information Access Clinic. He holds a J.D. from Yale Law School and a B.M. and B.A. from Oberlin College.</p>
</section>
